  I'm working my way through 40th doing just this.  Halfway through 40th and I've made over 1000pp from the giants.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Ruatha Kneeslasher &lt;Wings of Honor&gt;<BR>40th Level Gnome Warriorette<BR><I>That which does not kill me jolly well won't be getting a second chance.</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Darodar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Now that I have out leveled this area, I'll release the secret.<P><B>OGGOK</B><P>Not the newbie guards outside the city.  Inside!<P>Went from 36-45 in there.  Went to SolB and LGuk for items mostly.<P>Started out level 36 with 300 plat in the bank.  3 1/2 weeks later I'm level 45 with 4500 plat in the bank and a shiny new tinkerers bag to boot!  Constant pulls, zone line 5 feet away.  You can sell 20 feet from where you are fighting (if you have guise / rogue / enchanter / wolfform).<P>Admittedly, it's not the most exciting battle in the world, but the money is very good (4-600 plat per night usually), and the exp rocks.  Also, once you get used to it, and can pull singles at will, it is a great place to work up those forgotten weapons skills.  Went from 0 to 121 1H blunt in a single night!<P>I am not trying to start another post on the ethics of guard killing, so please don't go there.  Just trying to help a fellow tank get out of hell.<P>By the way, they are still blue at 45, but I am a few levels behind my friends, so I left shortly after I started the final hell.<P><B>Darodar Steelstorm<BR>45 Warrior<BR><I>Society of Shadows  -  Prexus</I></B></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Immudan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Actually I've found it MUCH easier now that I'm past 45.  Before that I had trouble getting into a group when I showed up in Lguk without a prearranged one.  Now when I show up I normally get in right away.  Incidently, I made it through all my hell levels except for 35 in 2 days each (35 took a month, ugh).  I can still get an entire level in 1 day (did it last night).  It's all about a good group baby  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif">  So hang in there, you're almost out of the woods.  <P>BTW don't tell anyone but if you want an easier time getting into a group, call in sick, grab a thermos of coffee and get on at about 3am  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif">  I was in Lguk once last week when there were only 14 people there!  I knew there had to be some advantage to working graveyard shift...<P>------------------<BR>Khumak - 47 Ogre Warrior<BR>Hasima - 8 Dark Elf Necro<BR>Immudan - 11 Erudite Wizard<BR>(Rodcet Nife)</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
